    • Method Detail

      • setOperations

        public AuditRecordsTypes.FilterSpec.Builder setOperations(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> operations)
        List of audit records that match the given operations An operation in operations can be any of
        • Import
        • Export
        • Remediate
        • Checkcompliance
        • Precheck
        • Transition-Enable
        • Draft-List
        • Draft-Create
        • Draft-ImportFromHost
        • Draft-Get
        • Draft-ExportConfig
        • Draft-Update
        • Draft-ShowChanges
        • Draft-CheckCompliance
        • Draft-Precheck
        • Draft-Delete
        • Draft-Apply
        . This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.2.0. If null or empty, records with any operation match the filter.
        Parameters:
        operations - New value for the property.

      • setUsernames

        public AuditRecordsTypes.FilterSpec.Builder setUsernames(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> usernames)
        List of audit records that match the given users. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.2.0. If null or empty, records with any users match the filter.
        Parameters:
        usernames - New value for the property.

      • setTimeDuration

        public AuditRecordsTypes.FilterSpec.Builder setTimeDuration(AuditRecordsTypes.FilterSpec.Timeframe timeDuration)
        List of audit records that match Timeframe, valid values are THREE_MONTHS, SIX_MONTHS, YEAR, CUSTOM. i.e. For ex: records within last 3 months. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.2.0. If null or empty, last one year audit records match the filter.
        Parameters:
        timeDuration - New value for the property.

      • setTimePeriod

        public AuditRecordsTypes.FilterSpec.Builder setTimePeriod(AuditRecordsTypes.TimePeriod timePeriod)
        List of audit records that match the given start time i.e. occurred after the AuditRecordsTypes.TimePeriod.getStart() and the given end time i.e. before the AuditRecordsTypes.TimePeriod.getEnd(). This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.2.0. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getTimeDuration() is AuditRecordsTypes.FilterSpec.Timeframe.CUSTOM.
        Parameters:
        timePeriod - New value for the property.
